@page "/modules/datamodeling"
@using System.Text.Json
@inject DataModelingApiClient Api
@inject BenchmarkService Benchmark
@implements IDisposable

<PageTitle>Data Modeling - Learn Cosmos DB</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Data Modeling</h1>
    <span class="page-subtitle">A guided walkthrough of document modeling in Azure Cosmos DB</span>
</div>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 1 — About
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2>About Data Modeling in Azure Cosmos DB</h2>
    <p>
        While there are multiple considerations in Cosmos DB for optimizing performance, understanding
        <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/modeling-data" target="_blank">data modeling</a>
        and implementing it effectively can be critical in getting the best experience. This walkthrough reviews different
        methods of modeling in Cosmos DB and demonstrates the benefits of thinking in a non-relational way. Note there is
        no one size fits all — the demo itself unveils multiple methods as we progress through it.
    </p>

    <h3>Scenario</h3>
    <p>
        Consider a media streaming site that wants a fast browsing experience for users located around the world.
        Movie information is created by studios and is generally consistent, but the flexibility of being schema-less is also
        a need. Cosmos DB, as a NoSQL database, allows us to adjust the schema as needed without redefining the entire
        database schema like you might need in a relational database.
    </p>
    <p>
        The browsing pattern we are optimizing for: a user searches a movie title, the results show a director,
        they click the director to see other movies, then select a movie from those results. We will walk through four
        different document models — each using the <strong>same data and same partition key</strong> — and see how
        the RU cost changes dramatically based on how the data is structured.
    </p>
    <p>
        At any given time there are ~1,000 concurrent users performing searches, so for cost calculations consider the
        query cost × 1,000.
    </p>

    @if (hints is not null)
    {
        <div class="guide-callout">
            <strong>Your search values for this session:</strong>
            Movie: <strong>@hints.MovieTitle</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Director: <strong>@hints.TopDirectorName</strong>
            <br/><span style="font-size: 0.8rem; opacity: 0.7;">Refresh the page to get new random values.</span>
        </div>
    }
    else
    {
        <div class="guide-callout">Loading search values…</div>
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 2 — Single Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2>Starting Model — "Single"</h2>
    <p>
        To try and balance our partitions, we went with a
        <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/partitioning-overview#choose-partitionkey" target="_blank">partitioning</a>
        method of using the movie title as our partition key. Each document in our collection is a single movie.
    </p>
    <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "1234567890",
    "type": "movie",
    "title": "single doc movie",
    "originalTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "tagline": "A great tagline",
    "description": "A movie about data modeling.",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg",
    "genres": [
        {
            "name": "Action",
            "id": "g001"
        }
    ],
    "directors": [
        {
            "name": "best director",
            "originalName": "Best Director",
            "id": "0987654321"
        }
    ],
    "actors": [
        {
            "name": "best actor",
            "originalName": "Best Actor",
            "id": "1029384576"
        }
    ],
    "reviews": [
        {
            "id": "r001",
            "criticReview": "A thrilling ride.",
            "criticScore": 8.5
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    <p>
        Since a user does not know the unique ID of a movie, searching on a movie title allows a partition-based query
        with lower RU cost. However, searching for a director or actor is embedded information — it requires a cross-partition
        <code>ARRAY_CONTAINS</code> query and the user must specify the search type (movie vs. person).
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Try it:</strong> Walk through the three steps below to see the RU cost at each stage.
    </p>

    @{ var single = sections["Single"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(single, "Single")

    @{ var singleActive = GetActiveResponse(single); }
    @if (singleActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> This query searches on the movie title, which is the partition key. This means the
                query is scoped to a single partition — the cheapest type of SQL query at ~3 RU.
            </div>
        }
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> The Single model required a <code>searchType=person</code> parameter and used an
                <code>ARRAY_CONTAINS</code> cross-partition query — significantly more expensive than the movie search.
            </div>
        }
        @if (singleActive.Label == "Movie Select (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Since we know the exact document ID and partition key from the previous results,
                this is a point read — the cheapest possible operation at ~1 RU.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(singleActive.Response, singleActive.Label)
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 3 — Embedded Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2>Embedded Model</h2>
    <p>
        We improved searching by creating a collocated document for each Actor and Director for a given movie. The data is
        embedded just like the movie document with some minor changes to properties. This simplified application logic and
        improved user experience — <strong>no need to specify a search type</strong>. The movie documents remain unchanged.
    </p>
    <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "mov12345act6789",
    "type": "person",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "movieId": "1234567890",
    "movieTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "tagline": "A great tagline",
    "description": "A movie about data modeling.",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg",
    "genres": [
        {
            "name": "Action",
            "id": "g001"
        }
    ],
    "directors": [
        {
            "name": "best director",
            "originalName": "Best Director",
            "id": "0987654321"
        }
    ],
    "actors": [
        {
            "name": "best actor",
            "originalName": "Best Actor",
            "id": "1029384576"
        }
    ],
    "reviews": [
        {
            "id": "r001",
            "criticReview": "A thrilling ride.",
            "criticScore": 8.5
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    <p>
        Because we query on a partition value (the person's name), the director search cost is reduced significantly.
        However, these person documents duplicate the full movie data, increasing storage from ~500MB to ~3GB.
        The storage cost increase is minimal (~$0.75) compared to the RU savings.
    </p>

    @{ var embedded = sections["Embedded"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(embedded, "Embedded")

    @{ var embeddedActive = GetActiveResponse(embedded); }
    @if (embeddedActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> The movie search is identical to the Single model — same partition-key query,
                same RU cost. The Embedded model only improves person searches.
            </div>
        }
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> No <code>searchType</code> needed — the query is a simple partition-key lookup
                on the director's name. Compare this RU cost to the Single model's director search above.
            </div>
        }
        @if (embeddedActive.Label == "Movie Select (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Point read on the movie document using ID and partition key — same ~1 RU cost
                as the Single model.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(embeddedActive.Response, embeddedActive.Label)
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 4 — Reference Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2>Reference Model</h2>
    <p>
        To reduce RU cost further, we used the same collocation method but changed the person documents to only contain
        basic reference data for the movie. This greatly reduced document size and made them more consistent.
    </p>
    <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "mov12345act6789",
    "type": "person",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "movieId": "1234567890",
    "movieTitle": "Single Doc Movie",
    "mpaaRating": "PG-13",
    "releaseDate": "2001-06-15",
    "year": 2001,
    "posterUrl": "https://example.com/poster.jpg"
}</pre>
    <p>
        We lose embedded details like genres and reviews, but those were not used during browsing. The smaller
        documents result in slightly lower RU costs.
    </p>

    @{ var reference = sections["Reference"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(reference, "Reference")

    @{ var referenceActive = GetActiveResponse(reference); }
    @if (referenceActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Movie search is the same partition-key query — the movie documents are unchanged
                across all models.
            </div>
        }
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> The Reference model uses slimmer person documents with only basic movie data.
                The smaller document size results in a slightly lower RU cost compared to the Embedded model.
            </div>
        }
        @if (referenceActive.Label == "Movie Select (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Point read retrieves the full movie document — same cost as other models since
                the movie documents are identical across all four containers.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(referenceActive.Response, referenceActive.Label)
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 5 — Hybrid Model
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section">
    <h2>Hybrid Model</h2>
    <p>
        By combining the partition-based query approach from the Embedded model with the smaller document size from
        the Reference model, we designed a hybrid document. Each person has a <strong>single document</strong> containing
        a <code>roles</code> array with reference data for each movie. This can be obtained with a partition query or
        even a Point Read.
    </p>
    <pre class="doc-json">{
    "id": "act123",
    "title": "best actor",
    "originalTitle": "Best Actor",
    "type": "person",
    "roles": [
        {
            "movieId": "13579",
            "movieTitle": "Movie 1",
            "mpaaRating": "PG",
            "releaseDate": "1901-03-10",
            "year": 1901,
            "posterUrl": "https://example.com/movie1.jpg",
            "roleName": "Lead Hero"
        },
        {
            "movieId": "24680",
            "movieTitle": "Movie 2",
            "mpaaRating": "R",
            "releaseDate": "1902-07-22",
            "year": 1902,
            "posterUrl": "https://example.com/movie2.jpg",
            "roleName": "Villain"
        }
    ]
}</pre>
    <p>
        The director search cost drops to nearly match the movie search cost. Once a user starts browsing by
        clicking results, subsequent queries can be Point Reads — roughly 1-2 RU each.
    </p>

    @{ var hybrid = sections["Hybrid"]; }
    @RenderStepButtons(hybrid, "Hybrid")

    @{ var hybridActive = GetActiveResponse(hybrid); }
    @if (hybridActive.Response is not null)
    {
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Movie Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Movie search remains the same partition-key query across all models.
                The real gains in the Hybrid model come from the director search.
            </div>
        }
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Director Search")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> The director search is now nearly as cheap as a movie search — a single person
                document contains all movie references in a <code>roles</code> array. Compare the costs in the table below.
            </div>
        }
        @if (hybridActive.Label == "Movie Select (Point Read)")
        {
            <div class="guide-callout guide-callout-info">
                <strong>Info:</strong> Point read on the selected movie. With the Hybrid model, once a user starts
                browsing by clicking results, every subsequent query can be a Point Read at ~1 RU each.
            </div>
        }
        @RenderResultsPanel(hybridActive.Response, hybridActive.Label)
    }
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Section 6 — Summary
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section class="guide-section guide-section-last">
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
        By rethinking our data model and taking advantage of the schema-less design of Cosmos DB, we were able to take the
        same data and even the same partition key and achieve a vastly improved performance experience by modeling the data
        to fit the use case.
    </p>
    <p>
        Given the scenario of 1,000 concurrent users performing these actions, the Hybrid model achieves over <strong>2.5×</strong>
        performance improvement — resulting in over <strong>60%</strong> service cost reduction while also providing an
        improved application experience with richer browsing data.
    </p>
    <p>
        There is no one-size-fits-all solution, but you will find there are many ways to get great performance out of
        Cosmos DB with data modeling. Review the cost comparison table below to see your results from this walkthrough.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="/demos/datamodeling" class="guide-demo-link">Open the free-play demo →</a>
        to explore all four models with your own search values.
    </p>
    <p style="opacity: 0.6; font-size: 0.85rem;">
        <em>This scenario was tested with <a href="https://www.imdb.com/">IMDB</a> data available at the time. The
        document counts for the interactive demo may differ from the original millions-scale dataset.</em>
    </p>
</section>

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Floating Cost Comparison Table
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
@if (HasAnyCosts())
{
    <div class="guide-cost-tracker">
        <div class="cost-tracker-header">
            <span class="cost-tracker-title">Cost Comparison</span>
            <button class="benchmark-clear" title="Reset all costs" @onclick="ResetAll">↺</button>
        </div>
        <table class="cost-table">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Model</th>
                    @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                    {
                        <th>@action</th>
                    }
                    <th>Total</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                @foreach (var model in Benchmark.ModelNames)
                {
                    @if (Benchmark.GetModelTotal(model) > 0)
                    {
                        <tr>
                            <td>@model</td>
                            @foreach (var action in Benchmark.ActionNames)
                            {
                                var cost = Benchmark.GetCost(model, action);
                                <td class="@(cost > 0 ? "cost-active" : "")">@cost.ToString("F2") RU</td>
                            }
                            @{ var total = Benchmark.GetModelTotal(model); }
                            <td class="cost-total @(total > 0 ? "cost-active" : "")"><strong>@total.ToString("F2") RU</strong></td>
                        </tr>
                    }
                }
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
}

@* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Render Fragments
   ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
@{
    RenderFragment RenderStepButtons(SectionState sec, string model) => __builder2 =>
    {
        var isMovie = sec.Step == SectionStep.Ready;
        var isDirector = sec.Step == SectionStep.MovieDone;
        var isDetail = sec.Step == SectionStep.DirectorDone;
        var isDone = sec.Step == SectionStep.DetailDone;
        var isWorking = sec.IsLoading;

        <div class="guide-step-row">
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isMovie ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isMovie || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoMovieSearch(model)">
                @StepLabel("1. Search Movie", isWorking && isMovie, sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready)
            </button>
            <span class="guide-step-arrow">→</span>
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.MovieDone ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isDirector ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isDirector || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoDirectorSearch(model)">
                @StepLabel("2. Search Director", isWorking && isDirector, sec.Step > SectionStep.MovieDone)
            </button>
            <span class="guide-step-arrow">→</span>
            <button class="guide-step-btn @(sec.Step > SectionStep.DirectorDone ? "guide-step-done" : "") @(isDetail ? "guide-step-active" : "")"
                    disabled="@(!isDetail || isWorking)"
                    @onclick="() => DoDetailClick(model)">
                @StepLabel("3. Click Movie", isWorking && isDetail, sec.Step > SectionStep.DirectorDone)
            </button>

            @if (isDone || sec.Step > SectionStep.Ready)
            {
                <button class="guide-step-reset" title="Reset this section" @onclick="() => ResetSection(model)">↺</button>
            }
        </div>

        @if (sec.Error is not null)
        {
            <div class="error-message">@(sec.Error)</div>
        }
    };

    RenderFragment RenderResultsPanel(DataModelingResponse resp, string label) => __builder2 =>
    {
        <div class="guide-results-label">@label</div>
        <div class="results-panel">
            <div class="panel panel-left">
                <div class="diag-summary">
                    <h3>Query Diagnostics</h3>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">RU Cost</span>
                        <span class="diag-value ru-highlight">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.RequestCharge RU</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Query Type</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryType</span>
                    </div>
                    @if (resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryText is not null)
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Query</span>
                            <span class="diag-value" style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.78rem;">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryText</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    @if (resp.RequestDiagnostics.QueryType == "Point Read")
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Document ID</span>
                            <span class="diag-value diag-truncate">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.DocId</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Partition Key</span>
                            <span class="diag-value diag-truncate">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.FormattedSearchValue</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        <div class="diag-row">
                            <span class="diag-label">Search Value</span>
                            <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.SubmittedSearchValue</span>
                        </div>
                    }
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Data Model</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.RequestDiagnostics.DataModel</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="diag-row">
                        <span class="diag-label">Documents</span>
                        <span class="diag-value">@resp.MediaResults.Count</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                @if (resp.MediaResults.Count > 0)
                {
                    <h3 style="margin-top: 1rem;">Raw JSON</h3>
                    <pre class="doc-json">@FormatJson(resp.MediaResults[0])</pre>
                }
            </div>

            <div class="panel-right">
                <div class="panel">
                    <h3>Results (@resp.MediaResults.Count)</h3>
                    <div class="poster-grid">
                        @foreach (var json in resp.MediaResults)
                        {
                            var docType = GetProp(json, "type") ?? "movie";

                            @if (docType == "movie")
                            {
                                var displayTitle = GetProp(json, "originalTitle") ?? GetProp(json, "title") ?? "";
                                var year = GetProp(json, "year") ?? "";
                                var rating = GetProp(json, "mpaaRating") ?? "";
                                var poster = GetProp(json, "posterUrl");

                                <div class="poster-card">
                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(poster))
                                    {
                                        <img class="poster-img" src="@poster" alt="@displayTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                    }
                                    else
                                    {
                                        <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                    }
                                    <div class="poster-info">
                                        <div class="poster-title">@displayTitle</div>
                                        <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(year)) { <span class="poster-year">@year</span> }
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(rating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@rating</span> }
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            }
                            else if (docType == "person")
                            {
                                var movieTitle = GetProp(json, "movieTitle") ?? "";
                                var poster = GetProp(json, "posterUrl");
                                var releaseDate = GetProp(json, "releaseDate") ?? "";
                                var rating = GetProp(json, "mpaaRating") ?? "";
                                var roles = GetRoles(json);

                                @if (roles.Count > 0)
                                {
                                    @foreach (var role in roles)
                                    {
                                        <div class="poster-card">
                                            @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.PosterUrl))
                                            {
                                                <img class="poster-img" src="@role.PosterUrl" alt="@role.MovieTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                            }
                                            else
                                            {
                                                <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                            }
                                            <div class="poster-info">
                                                <div class="poster-title">@role.MovieTitle</div>
                                                <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.Year)) { <span class="poster-year">@role.Year</span> }
                                                    @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(role.MpaaRating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@role.MpaaRating</span> }
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    }
                                }
                                else
                                {
                                    <div class="poster-card">
                                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(poster))
                                        {
                                            <img class="poster-img" src="@poster" alt="@movieTitle" loading="lazy" />
                                        }
                                        else
                                        {
                                            <div class="poster-img-placeholder">🎬</div>
                                        }
                                        <div class="poster-info">
                                            <div class="poster-title">@movieTitle</div>
                                            <div class="poster-meta-row">
                                                @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(releaseDate)) { <span class="poster-year">@releaseDate</span> }
                                                @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(rating)) { <span class="poster-rating">@rating</span> }
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    };
}

<style>
    .guide-section {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        padding-bottom: 2rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);
    }

    .guide-section-last {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    .guide-callout {
        background: var(--bg-panel-alt);
        border-left: 4px solid var(--cosmos-blue);
        padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .guide-callout-info {
        border-left-color: var(--cosmos-teal);
    }

    /* Step Buttons */
    .guide-step-row {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .guide-step-btn {
        padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem;
        border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
        border-radius: 6px;
        background: var(--bg-panel);
        color: var(--text-muted);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        cursor: not-allowed;
        transition: all 0.2s;
    }

    .guide-step-btn.guide-step-active {
        border-color: var(--cosmos-blue);
        color: var(--cosmos-blue);
        background: var(--bg-panel);
